the wizard may take one person out]

01:07:26.390 --> 01:07:29.650
[Rule 4: If the one who runs out
is the wizard, the wizard wins]

01:07:29.650 --> 01:07:32.910
[If a Ghost is mixed in, the Ghosts win]

01:07:34.540 --> 01:07:35.550
NuNew: Today I…

01:07:35.980 --> 01:07:37.800
NuNew: Actually, I was already very scared
before we even started.

01:07:37.800 --> 01:07:38.800
NuNew: This game…

01:07:39.520 --> 01:07:40.520
Goy: I feel like they've all
played for a long time.

01:07:40.520 --> 01:07:41.940
Goy: So they might
pretend to be clueless.

01:07:41.940 --> 01:07:43.440
Goy: I think this person
is super reliable.

01:07:43.440 --> 01:07:44.900
Ink: But Ice, be careful.
Someone might trick you.

01:07:44.900 --> 01:07:45.660
NuNew: Right.

01:07:45.660 --> 01:07:46.210
NuNew: Someone will definitely lie.

01:07:46.210 --> 01:07:47.260
Ink: Someone will definitely lie.

01:07:47.260 --> 01:07:49.190
Oat: Pretending to say who is what.

01:07:49.240 --> 01:07:50.700
Oat: It could also be a lie.

01:07:50.720 --> 01:07:51.580
Oat: If he lies,

01:07:52.140 --> 01:07:53.740
Oat: the wizard rips off the name tag. Bam!

01:07:53.740 --> 01:07:55.000
Oat: And he or she loses immediately.

01:07:55.000 --> 01:07:55.790
Jeff: Right now…

01:07:55.790 --> 01:07:56.590
Jeff: I think…

01:07:56.850 --> 01:07:57.840
Jeff: It's probably already very
difficult for me because

01:07:57.840 --> 01:07:59.790
Jeff: everyone may not trust me anymore.

01:07:59.790 --> 01:08:01.010
Ice: I've already set things
up in advance.

01:08:01.010 --> 01:08:03.730
Ice: We really want to win,
so we've been analyzing everything.

01:08:03.730 --> 01:08:05.790
Nont: Even if we die, we die together.

01:08:06.300 --> 01:08:09.100
Phuak: Today is all about
psychological warfare.

01:08:09.990 --> 01:08:14.060
[The chaotic clash between
wizards and Ghosts begins]

01:08:15.700 --> 01:08:17.430
Ice: Ink is probably the witch.

01:08:17.479 --> 01:08:19.410
Ice: Phuak is probably the wizard.

01:08:19.850 --> 01:08:21.210
Phuak: But the Ghosts…

01:08:21.210 --> 01:08:22.880
Phuak: No matter what,
they'll say they're the wizard.

01:08:22.880 --> 01:08:25.439
Phuak: So everyone will claim
to be the wizard.

01:08:25.439 --> 01:08:26.240
Phuak: Right.

01:08:26.840 --> 01:08:28.370
Phuak: Let's take a gamble.

01:08:28.500 --> 01:08:30.819
[Is it the confidence of a real wizard
or a way to confuse everyone?]

01:08:30.819 --> 01:08:32.880
Phuak: The game will end in 3 minutes.

01:08:33.359 --> 01:08:34.819
Oat: But do you believe it?

01:08:34.870 --> 01:08:36.200
Oat: Today my intuition

01:08:36.560 --> 01:08:37.760
Oat: keeps telling me

01:08:38.430 --> 01:08:40.109
Oat: that Jeff is the Ghost.

01:08:40.950 --> 01:08:41.550
Oat: Ink

01:08:44.020 --> 01:08:45.350
Oat: might be the witch.

01:08:46.029 --> 01:08:46.680
Oat: Goy…

01:08:48.029 --> 01:08:48.100
Oat: Goy is someone I like.

01:08:48.100 --> 01:08:49.270
[I actually kind of have a crush on Goy.
You saw the news, right?]

01:08:49.270 --> 01:08:50.600
Oat: You know about it, right?
You saw the news, right?

01:08:50.600 --> 01:08:52.279
Oat: You saw the news, right?
Mm-hmm, OK.

01:08:52.279 --> 01:08:52.630
[A small confession]

01:08:52.630 --> 01:08:53.890
Oat: Don't tell anyone.

01:08:53.890 --> 01:08:55.010
Oat: I'm very shy.

01:08:57.180 --> 01:08:57.279
[The tragic fate of a secret admirer]

01:08:57.279 --> 01:08:58.279
Oat: I'm serious.

01:09:00.979 --> 01:09:04.020
[Is someone talking about me?]

01:09:05.270 --> 01:09:07.200
Goy: They say among these 4 people,

01:09:07.590 --> 01:09:08.689
Goy: the one who's the Ghost

01:09:08.689 --> 01:09:08.740
Goy: is Oat.

01:09:08.740 --> 01:09:10.310
[Oat might be the Ghost]

01:09:11.600 --> 01:09:12.800
Goy: I think it's him.

01:09:13.850 --> 01:09:16.450
Goy: I want to walk over and ask him,
"Is it you?"

01:09:18.700 --> 01:09:19.760
Goy: I'm the witch.

01:09:22.140 --> 01:09:22.229
[Is Goy a witch and Oat a wizard?]

01:09:22.229 --> 01:09:23.260
Goy: It's not Oat.

01:09:23.430 --> 01:09:24.490
Goy: Probably not.

01:09:27.220 --> 01:09:30.189
[What about NuNew's role?]

01:09:30.189 --> 01:09:31.260
NuNew: In the first 2 episodes,

01:09:31.260 --> 01:09:32.609
NuNew: actually, in the first 3 episodes,
the name tag ripping game

01:09:32.609 --> 01:09:33.970
really scared me.

01:09:33.970 --> 01:09:36.229
NuNew: But today I'm not afraid anymore.

01:09:40.750 --> 01:09:42.750
NuNew: The first clue I got is…

01:09:43.319 --> 01:09:47.890
[Among the Ghosts, there are members of
the Running Man team and also guests,]

01:09:47.890 --> 01:09:52.460
[and among them there is someone who have
defeated the Running Man team before]

01:09:52.790 --> 01:09:54.790
NuNew: Jeff wins in every episode.

01:09:58.400 --> 01:10:01.080
NuNew: Ink won the second
and third episodes.

01:10:03.140 --> 01:10:04.170
NuNew: Jeff and Ink.

01:10:04.170 --> 01:10:06.430
NuNew: One of these two must be the Ghost.

01:10:06.730 --> 01:10:11.580
[Is the Ghost Ink or Jeff?]

01:10:11.800 --> 01:10:14.200
Jeff: My name tag has never
been ripped off.

01:10:15.040 --> 01:10:17.340
Jeff: I've already been the winner
for 3 consecutive weeks.

01:10:17.340 --> 01:10:20.340
Jeff: I think this episode
won't be difficult either.

01:10:23.530 --> 01:10:23.870
Goy: Got…

01:10:23.870 --> 01:10:28.060
PD: The Name Tag Ripping Ghost-Hunting Operation
is about to begin.

01:10:28.120 --> 01:10:29.270
5.

01:10:29.600 --> 01:10:31.320
Ice: Is it starting? Is it starting now?

01:10:31.320 --> 01:10:32.220
4.

01:10:35.190 --> 01:10:36.190
3.

01:10:39.120 --> 01:10:40.130
2.

01:10:42.270 --> 01:10:43.440
1.

01:10:43.820 --> 01:10:46.020
Phuak: Today is all about psychological warfare.

01:10:46.020 --> 01:10:47.190
Run.

01:10:48.180 --> 01:10:49.700
NuNew: I'm starting!

01:10:50.300 --> 01:10:51.300
NuNew: Fighting!

01:10:51.560 --> 01:10:53.560
NuNew: Everyone, go look for clues.

01:10:53.970 --> 01:10:55.430
NuNew: We have to be quick.

01:10:56.720 --> 01:10:58.580
NuNew: The elevator is over here.

01:10:58.600 --> 01:10:58.980
NuNew: Let's search first.

01:10:58.980 --> 01:11:01.790
[The Ghost elevator is on the first floor]

01:11:01.790 --> 01:11:02.990
NuNew: Nothing here.

01:11:03.070 --> 01:11:05.000
NuNew: Are there any clues nearby?

01:11:05.150 --> 01:11:06.010
NuNew: Really?

01:11:10.040 --> 01:11:12.300
NuNew: Something just caught in my hair.

01:11:16.190 --> 01:11:17.450
NuNew: What's up here?

01:11:19.240 --> 01:11:20.240
NuNew: Oh-no. Ah!

01:11:20.340 --> 01:11:22.000
NuNew: Is this from the staff?

01:11:23.350 --> 01:11:24.150
NuNew: Sorry.

01:11:27.750 --> 01:11:28.680
NuNew: Nothing.

01:11:29.090 --> 01:11:30.750
NuNew: Let's keep searching.

01:11:32.230 --> 01:11:34.540
[What about Jeff on the third floor?]

01:11:38.990 --> 01:11:41.660
[He found the clue right away!]

01:11:45.470 --> 01:11:47.570
Jeff: It says among
the Running Man members…

01:11:47.570 --> 01:11:48.650
Jeff: That would be me.

01:11:48.650 --> 01:11:50.580
Jeff: Among the Running Man members,

01:11:50.580 --> 01:11:52.370
Jeff: someone who has won before.

01:11:52.370 --> 01:11:58.180
[Judging from his performance,
Jeff is very likely a Ghost]

01:12:02.350 --> 01:12:04.820
[He keeps finding more clue cards]

01:12:17.170 --> 01:12:18.870
Ink: The most important thing
right now is to find clues first.

01:12:18.870 --> 01:12:20.330
Ink: Find the clues first.

01:12:39.060 --> 01:12:39.920
Ink: Found one.

01:12:42.000 --> 01:12:47.620
[There are both "male Ghosts" and "female Ghosts"]

01:12:48.900 --> 01:12:52.100
[So is the Ghost Ink or Goy?]

01:12:57.440 --> 01:12:59.370
Nont: This shouldn't be it, right?

01:13:02.180 --> 01:13:04.360
Nont: There's nothing behind here either.

01:13:04.360 --> 01:13:05.360
Nont: Seriously?

01:13:06.120 --> 01:13:08.180
Nont: Are the clues this hard to find?

01:13:10.840 --> 01:13:11.840
Ice: Nothing.

01:13:18.350 --> 01:13:19.580
Ice: They're really hard to find.

01:13:19.580 --> 01:13:21.220
Ice: I just looked around earlier.

01:13:21.220 --> 01:13:23.490
Ice: I checked this whole floor,
but there was nothing.

01:13:23.490 --> 01:13:25.420
Ice: Maybe they're inside the rooms.

01:13:25.420 --> 01:13:28.900
[The guests still can't
find any clue cards…]

01:13:29.180 --> 01:13:32.620
[Meanwhile, how is the other
guest, Goy, doing?]

01:13:34.260 --> 01:13:35.260
Goy: What is this?

01:13:37.010 --> 01:13:40.980
[Goy quickly adapts to the game]

01:13:44.970 --> 01:13:45.680
Goy: Jeff.

01:13:48.100 --> 01:13:52.860
A Ghost has debuted
for more than 10 years.
[New clue: a Ghost debuted
more than 10 years ago]

01:13:53.770 --> 01:13:55.840
Goy: Debuted more than 10 years ago.

01:13:56.640 --> 01:13:58.300
Goy: People who debuted
more than 10 years ago…

01:13:58.300 --> 01:13:59.870
Goy: People who debuted
more than 10 years ago…

01:13:59.870 --> 01:14:02.360
Goy: Ink, Jeff, and Oat.

01:14:02.940 --> 01:14:03.800
Goy: That's it.

01:14:03.850 --> 01:14:04.880
Goy: Three people.

01:14:04.880 --> 01:14:05.980
Goy: The others don't count.

01:14:05.980 --> 01:14:07.840
Goy: Because several people here

01:14:08.890 --> 01:14:10.700
Goy: have debuted for more than 10 years.

01:14:10.700 --> 01:14:11.760
Goy: My head hurts.

01:14:12.300 --> 01:14:13.500
Goy: This is too hard.

01:14:13.750 --> 01:14:18.460
[There are 2 Ghosts, but their identities
are becoming more and more mysterious]

01:14:19.140 --> 01:14:21.140
NuNew: I'm alone on the first floor.

01:14:21.860 --> 01:14:25.940
[Better hurry upstairs and find everyone!]

01:14:31.070 --> 01:14:31.770
NuNew: Ink.

01:14:32.150 --> 01:14:33.500
Ink: What's wrong, NuNew?

01:14:33.500 --> 01:14:35.160
NuNew: Did you find anything?

01:14:36.760 --> 01:14:38.690
NuNew: Huh? You already found one?

01:14:38.900 --> 01:14:39.400
[Ink casually says, "I found one."]

01:14:39.400 --> 01:14:41.330
NuNew: Huh? You already found one?

01:14:43.300 --> 01:14:46.100
-NuNew: Ink, did you bring the clue card?
-Ink: I brought it.

01:14:46.100 --> 01:14:46.980
NuNew: You brought it too?

01:14:46.980 --> 01:14:47.800
Ink: Yes.

01:14:47.800 --> 01:14:50.020
Ink: Do you want to take the clue from me?

01:14:50.400 --> 01:14:54.140
[NuNew is still unsure]

01:14:54.540 --> 01:14:59.980
[So the two split up again
to search for clues]

01:15:00.650 --> 01:15:02.170
Ink: The clue I found says…

01:15:02.570 --> 01:15:05.030
Ink: There is a male ghost and a female ghost.

01:15:05.180 --> 01:15:06.840
Ink: NuNew is eavesdropping.

01:15:10.200 --> 01:15:12.660
NuNew: I've started to
suspect Ink because…

01:15:13.130 --> 01:15:14.430
NuNew: So I thought…

01:15:14.900 --> 01:15:17.350
NuNew: If the person who took
the clue is the Ghost,

01:15:17.350 --> 01:15:19.750
NuNew: they might not
want others to see it.

01:15:19.930 --> 01:15:22.190
NuNew: So they might hide the clue first.

01:15:22.920 --> 01:15:23.420
Ink: Oh, OK.

01:15:23.420 --> 01:15:29.020
[Is Ink a witch or a Ghost?]

01:15:45.820 --> 01:15:46.580
Oat: Hey.

01:15:46.580 --> 01:15:47.810
Oat: Oh!

01:15:52.220 --> 01:15:54.550
-Jeff: Did you find anything?
-NuNew: No.

01:15:54.990 --> 01:15:57.190
NuNew: What are you guys talking about?

01:15:57.750 --> 01:15:58.810
Oat: You scared me!

01:16:05.220 --> 01:16:07.280
Jeff: The Ghost is a… host.

01:16:07.720 --> 01:16:08.510
Jeff: A host.

01:16:09.240 --> 01:16:11.040
Jeff: Responsible for hosting.

01:16:11.170 --> 01:16:13.190
Jeff: The Ghost is a… host.

01:16:13.540 --> 01:16:14.670
Jeff: A host.

01:16:15.020 --> 01:16:16.760
Jeff: Responsible for hosting.

01:16:16.760 --> 01:16:17.970
Jeff: The clue says they used to be a host.

01:16:17.970 --> 01:16:20.250
Jeff: And they have accessories on them.

01:16:20.250 --> 01:16:22.370
Jeff: The clue says they used to be a host.

01:16:22.370 --> 01:16:22.430
[The clue Jeff received
says that among them]

01:16:22.430 --> 01:16:25.640
Jeff: It says the Ghost is among the members.
Then isn't that me?

01:16:25.640 --> 01:16:25.650
Jeff: Among the Running Man members,
someone who has won before.

01:16:25.650 --> 01:16:28.940
[there is someone
who has won on Running Man…]

01:16:29.500 --> 01:16:31.800
[Jeff crosses out the clue
that is unfavorable to him]

01:16:31.800 --> 01:16:34.100
[and changes the subject]

01:16:34.440 --> 01:16:35.550
Jeff: If we…

01:16:35.550 --> 01:16:37.380
Jeff: We are all hosts…

01:16:37.660 --> 01:16:38.320
Oat: Right.

01:16:39.260 --> 01:16:40.250
Ice: Did you find anything?

01:16:40.250 --> 01:16:40.730
Oat: What?

01:16:40.730 --> 01:16:41.810
Ice: Did you find anything?

01:16:41.810 --> 01:16:42.460
Oat: I did.

01:16:42.460 --> 01:16:43.160
Ice: You found something?

01:16:43.160 --> 01:16:44.090
Oat: Right here.

01:16:44.320 --> 01:16:44.910
Ice: Huh?

01:16:44.910 --> 01:16:46.020
Oat: Everyone has found something.

01:16:46.020 --> 01:16:48.190
Ice: I can't find anything at all.
How did you find it?

01:16:48.190 --> 01:16:49.190
Jeff: What we're talking about is

01:16:49.190 --> 01:16:50.700
Jeff: someone who once served as a host.

01:16:50.700 --> 01:16:51.860
Jeff: Someone here.

01:16:51.860 --> 01:16:52.800
Jeff: Here, here, here.

01:16:52.800 --> 01:16:53.660
Jeff: This show

01:16:53.780 --> 01:16:55.510
Jeff: gathers hosts together.

01:16:55.570 --> 01:16:56.750
Ice: Oh.

01:16:57.700 --> 01:16:59.040
NuNew: But it might not mean that.

01:16:59.040 --> 01:17:01.480
Jeff: But it says "once,"
so it might not mean now.

01:17:01.480 --> 01:17:02.500
NuNew: It might not mean that.

01:17:02.500 --> 01:17:05.140
Jeff: But it says "once,"
so it might not mean now.

01:17:05.140 --> 01:17:09.010
[As soon as he's suspected,
Jeff quickly changes his statement]

01:17:13.220 --> 01:17:13.900
Jeff: OK, OK. I'll go look for more clues.

01:17:13.900 --> 01:17:15.080
[Everyone decides to search for
more hints so they split up again]

01:17:15.080 --> 01:17:16.280
Jeff: OK, OK.

01:17:17.990 --> 01:17:18.980
NuNew: Oat, Goy.

01:17:19.140 --> 01:17:19.520
NuNew: Oat.

01:17:19.520 --> 01:17:20.520
Goy: Did you find anything?

01:17:20.520 --> 01:17:21.130
NuNew: I'm not sure.

01:17:21.130 --> 01:17:22.360
NuNew: Oat, Oat.

01:17:23.920 --> 01:17:26.200
NuNew: I saw the clue
after the second game victory,

01:17:26.200 --> 01:17:27.940
NuNew: the clue
from the paint-splash game.

01:17:27.940 --> 01:17:28.860
NuNew: The clue says

01:17:28.860 --> 01:17:30.100
NuNew: one of the Ghosts is

01:17:30.100 --> 01:17:32.830
NuNew: someone who has won
on Running Man before.

01:17:33.140 --> 01:17:34.480
NuNew: That means a main cast member.

01:17:34.480 --> 01:17:35.660
NuNew: In my opinion…

01:17:35.660 --> 01:17:37.370
NuNew: No, actually there
are only 2 possibilities.

01:17:37.370 --> 01:17:38.460
NuNew: Ink and Jeff.

01:17:38.460 --> 01:17:39.580
NuNew: That's why I
didn't share it earlier.

01:17:39.580 --> 01:17:40.970
NuNew: Only those two.

01:17:41.200 --> 01:17:42.260
NuNew: One of them.

01:17:43.200 --> 01:17:44.060
Oat: That's it.

01:17:44.390 --> 01:17:45.720
Oat: No one else has won.

01:17:46.410 --> 01:17:46.960
Oat: So…

01:17:47.210 --> 01:17:49.470
Oat: I'll keep this information for now.

01:17:52.810 --> 01:17:55.580
[At that moment, Jeff
is observing that group]

01:17:57.890 --> 01:17:59.680
Jeff: Let me tell you what
they're talking about over there.

01:17:59.680 --> 01:18:00.760
Jeff: They said...

01:18:01.350 --> 01:18:02.680
Jeff: NuNew wants to say

01:18:02.780 --> 01:18:03.860
Jeff: that I'm the Ghost.

01:18:03.860 --> 01:18:05.590
Jeff: Because the clue he got is

01:18:06.100 --> 01:18:06.720
Jeff: that

01:18:07.060 --> 01:18:08.950
Jeff: someone who has won
in Running Man before.

01:18:08.950 --> 01:18:12.070
Jeff: And the only person
who has won more than 3 rounds is me.

01:18:12.070 --> 01:18:21.000
[What will happen to these two?]

01:18:22.910 --> 01:18:23.500
Oat: But now

01:18:23.500 --> 01:18:25.560
Oat: I already know who the wizard is.

01:18:25.650 --> 01:18:26.310
Oat: NuNew.

01:18:28.260 --> 01:18:30.520
Oat: Because just now,
when NuNew shared the clue,

01:18:30.520 --> 01:18:31.700
Oat: he sounded very certain, so…

01:18:31.700 --> 01:18:33.880
Oat: NuNew must be the wizard.

01:18:38.310 --> 01:18:40.570
Nont: But earlier we didn't come in here.

01:18:46.370 --> 01:18:46.970
Nont: Huh?

01:18:48.820 --> 01:18:50.350
Nont: Is this a hidden door?

01:18:51.460 --> 01:18:52.700
[Secret clue card and instant noodles]

01:18:52.700 --> 01:18:53.940
Nont: It's here!

01:18:58.850 --> 01:19:00.510
Ink: I smell instant noodles.

01:19:04.070 --> 01:19:04.730
Nont: Really?

01:19:04.730 --> 01:19:06.710
Ink: Are you making instant noodles?

01:19:06.710 --> 01:19:07.290
Nont: A clue.

01:19:07.290 --> 01:19:08.270
Ink: Got it.

01:19:08.460 --> 01:19:09.520
Nont: Got the clue.

01:19:10.390 --> 01:19:11.260
-Ink: Open it, hurry, open it!
-Nont: Let's check the clue.

01:19:11.260 --> 01:19:12.790
Nont: Let's check the clue.

01:19:14.060 --> 01:19:18.060
Ink: Whoever finishes this bowl
of instant noodles first gets the clue.

01:19:27.740 --> 01:19:32.100
[The tempting noodles
make them forget the game]

01:19:32.220 --> 01:19:33.750
[By enjoying food while eating,
they can also get a hint]

01:19:33.750 --> 01:19:36.280
Ink: Looks like it was obvious
from the start.

01:19:38.300 --> 01:19:40.620
[They hand the clue to Nont,
who finishes the noodles first]

01:19:42.580 --> 01:19:43.840
Nont: OK, I'll open it.

01:19:50.180 --> 01:19:50.980
Nont: It says…

01:19:51.820 --> 01:19:56.500
[New clue: one of the Ghosts was born
in an odd-numbered month]

01:19:57.000 --> 01:20:01.380
Nont: I'm sure it's Jeff.

01:20:01.920 --> 01:20:04.980
Nont: Maybe Jeff. Jeff and I
were born in the same month.

01:20:06.580 --> 01:20:07.340
Jeff: So…

01:20:07.620 --> 01:20:09.980
Jeff: He will doubt me,
but it doesn’t matter.

01:20:09.980 --> 01:20:11.060
Jeff: These two...

01:20:11.940 --> 01:20:12.700
Jeff: Used to a host.
